exif:ImageDescription: Nina Schmale, left, and fellow nursing student Tammy Siouchoff dressed for a school initiation skit to the song "Alley Cat," circa 1966. Nursing students were under strict rules during the 1960s, but still they found time for fun. Tammy Siouchoff remembers life with her fellow students before six of them and two visiting nurses were murdered in a neighboring townhouse on Chicago's South Side in 1966.
